Target: OntoWasteManagement is designed to represent and support the day-to-day waste management operations, ranging from handling collection requests and billing reports, meeting reporting requirements, to fleet and bin management.

Comment: A service that delivers an empty bin to the specified site.
Label: Bin delivery service

Comment: A service provided by an entity (such as a municipality or private company) that involves the collection, transportation, and disposal or recycling of waste materials from residential, commercial, or industrial sources.
Label: Waste collection service

Comment: A service that delivers an empty bin to the specified site and tows away the full bin to a disposal site. The bin will not be returned to the service site afterwards.
Label: Bin exchange service

Comment: A service that collects the bin containing waste from the service site and disposes the waste at the disposal site. The bin will not be returned to the service site afterwards.
Label: Tow away service

Comment: A service that brings an empty bin to collect the waste from the service site and disposes the waste at the disposal site.  The bin will not be returned to the service site afterwards.
Label: Touch and go service

Comment: A service that collects the bin containing waste from the service site and disposes the waste at the disposal site, before returning the newly emptied bin to the service site.
Label: Dump and return service

Comment: A service for the management, treatment, and disposal of waste that adheres to environmental regulations and promoting sustainability.
Label: Waste disposal service

Comment: A facility with waste disposal services.
Label: Waste disposal facility

Comment: A container used to carry and store waste.
Label: Bin

Comment: A bin capable of attaching to an OTC truck.
Label: Open Top Container Bin

Comment: An open top container bin with a length of 3 feet.
Label: 3-feet bin

Comment: An open top container bin with a length of 5 feet.
Label: 5-feet bin

Comment: An open top container bin with a length of 7 feet.
Label: 7-feet bin

Comment: An open top container bin with the ability to compact waste.
Label: Compactor bin

Comment: A versatile truck equipped with a hydraulic hooklift system, used for transporting various container types, including heavy industrial and commercial waste containers.
Label: Hooklift truck

Comment: A truck designed for municipal waste collection, featuring a rear-loading mechanism with a hydraulic lift to compact waste into the truck body.
Label: Rear end loader truck

Comment: A truck specifically designed and equipped to collect, transport, and sometimes sort recyclable materials from various collection points to recycling facilities.
Label: Recycling truck

Comment: Any material, substance, or by-product that is no longer useful or required after the completion of a process. It is typically discarded because it is considered worthless, defective, or surplus to requirements.
Label: Waste

Comment: Waste that contains a combination of different materials, that may or may not be difficult to identify and separate individual components.
Label: Mixed waste

Comment: The residual byproduct generated from the incineration of various materials, including municipal solid waste, hazardous waste, and industrial byproducts.   Ash waste typically contains concentrated trace metals and other inorganic compounds.
Label: Ash waste

Comment: A semi-solid slurry that accumulates as a byproduct of wastewater treatment processes. It consists of organic and inorganic materials, including water, microorganisms, and chemical residues.
Label: Sludge waste

Comment: Waste generated from the construction, renovation, and demolition of buildings, roads, and other structures.
Label: Construction and demolition waste

Comment: Discarded electrical or electronic devices, such as computers, mobile phones, household appliances, and medical equipment. E-waste can contain hazardous materials like lead and mercury.
Label: Electronic waste

Comment: Waste composed of iron and steel. These metals are magnetic and are commonly found in items like appliances, cars, and construction materials.
Label: Ferrous metal waste

Comment: Edible food that is discarded at the retail or consumption stages, often due to spoilage or overproduction.
Label: Food waste

Comment: Organic materials resulting from fish cleaning or processing, including flesh, skin, bones, and entrails.
Label: Fish waste

Comment: Waste comprised mainly of vegetable matter, which is capable of being decomposed by microorganisms.
Label: Vegetable waste

Comment: Discarded glass products, such as bottles and jars, which can be recycled into new glass products.
Label: Glass waste

Comment: Waste generated in orchards, parks, gardens, and roadside plants, including green foliage, branches, and leaves.
Label: Horticultural waste

Comment: The large, central part of a tree that is cut down and discarded during tree removal or logging activities.
Label: Tree trunk waste

Comment: Smaller limbs and twigs removed from trees during pruning or tree removal.
Label: Tree branches waste

Comment: Waste consisting of fallen leaves from trees and plants, often collected during seasonal cleanups.
Label: Leaves waste

Comment: Waste composed of metals that do not contain iron, such as aluminum, copper, and brass. These metals are not magnetic.
Label: Non-ferrous metal waste

Comment: Waste consisting of aluminum products, such as cans, foil, and packaging materials.
Label: Aluminium waste

Comment: Waste composed of stainless steel, which is an alloy of iron, chromium, and other elements, known for its corrosion resistance.
Label: Stainless steel waste

Comment: Waste consisting of copper products, such as wiring, plumbing pipes, and electronics components.
Label: Copper waste

Comment: Waste consisting of paper and cardboard materials, including office paper, newspapers, and packaging.
Label: Paper or cardboard waste

Comment: Waste composed of paper products, such as office paper, newspapers, and magazines.
Label: Paper waste

Comment: Waste consisting of used corrugated cardboard, often from packaging and shipping materials.
Label: Old corrugated cardboard waste

Comment: Waste composed of plastic materials, including bottles, packaging, and containers.
Label: Plastics waste

Comment: Waste composed of polyethylene terephthalate materials, including beverage bottles and food containers.
Label: Polyethylene terephthalate (PET) waste

Comment: Waste composed of high-density polyethylene materials, including milk jugs, detergent bottles, and piping.
Label: High-density polyethylene (HDPE) waste

Comment: Waste composed of low-density polyethylene materials, including plastic bags, film wraps, and squeeze bottles.
Label: Low-density polyethylene (LDPE) waste

Comment: Waste composed of polypropylene materials, including packaging, automotive parts, and textiles.
Label: Polypropylene (PP) waste

Comment: Waste composed of polystyrene materials, including disposable food containers, packaging materials, and insulation.
Label: Polystyrene (PS) waste

Comment: Waste consisting of used and discarded tires from vehicles.
Label: Scrap tyres waste

Comment: Waste composed of textile and leather materials, including clothing, upholstery, and footwear.
Label: Textile or leather waste

Comment: Waste produced from the smelting and refining of metals, consisting of byproducts like slag.
Label: Used slag waste

Comment: Waste consisting of wood materials, including lumber, pallets, and furniture.
Label: Wood waste

Comment: Waste composed of wooden pallets used for shipping and storage.
Label: Pallet waste

Comment: Waste consisting of discarded furniture items, such as chairs, tables, and sofas.
Label: Furniture waste

Comment: Weight of a truck and its waste before any disposal.
Label: Gross truck weight

Comment: Weight of an empty truck after waste disposal.
Label: Unladen truck weight

Comment: Weight of the waste disposed, which is calculated through the difference of gross and unladen weight.
Label: Net waste weight

Comment: The current state of a bin.
Label: Bin status

Comment: A relationship describing the bin type for a series of waste services.
Label: has bin type

Comment: A relationship describing the waste category for a series of waste services.
Label: has waste type

Comment: A relationship assigning the bin to a service.
Label: has assigned bin

Comment: A relationship denoting the replacement bin for a service that will be delivered to the site.
Label: has replacement bin

Comment: A relationship describing the disposal charge of a waste disposal service.
Label: has disposal charge

Comment: A relationship describing the current bin status.
Label: has status

Comment: An identifier for a bin.
Label: has bin number
